definition.message:
There are 6 states for establishing a BGP session. When a session is established (state = 6), neighbors are able to exchange route information. Being stuck in any other state for too long suggests that there is something wrong with your BGP configuration, security rules, or network connectivity.

{{#is_alert}} 
{{snmp_device.name}} and {{neighbor.name}} are stuck in state {{value}} 
{{/is_alert}} 

{{#is_recovery}} 
{{snmp_device.name}} and {{neighbor.name}} are back to established state
{{/is_recovery}}
